                            <comment id="12534520" author="doronc" created="Sat, 13 Oct 2007 13:44:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for catching this Kyle.&lt;br/&gt;
Patch looks good to me and working.&lt;br/&gt;
I enhanced checkQuery() in test/a.o.l.search.QueryUtils to check all queries for serialization.&lt;br/&gt;
This catches this bug and verifies the fix.&lt;br/&gt;
It also shows that BoostingTermQuery fails fr this check, but I am not sure why.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12534555" author="doronc" created="Sat, 13 Oct 2007 17:57:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Correction - BoostingTermQuery is ok, but TestBTQ had to be modified for the serialization test to pass. &lt;br/&gt;
DisjunctionMaxQuery had problems similar to CustomScoreQuery.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12534556" author="doronc" created="Sat, 13 Oct 2007 18:17:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch contains:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Kyle&apos;s fixes for search.function weights.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;serialization test as part of standard queries tests,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fix for DisjunctionMaxQuery and for few tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12536615" author="doronc" created="Mon, 22 Oct 2007 11:01:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Just committed this fix. &lt;br/&gt;
Thanks Kyle!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
